## SECTION 2: CarrotCash Project Rules
*(Apply when working on the CarrotCash codebase)*

### Project Overview
CarrotCash is a micro-SaaS invoice and finance tracker
built for Indian freelancers and solopreneurs.

### Tech Stack
- Framework: React Native + Expo (SDK 55)
- Router: Expo Router (file-based)
- Backend: Supabase (auth + database + RLS)
- Language: TypeScript
- Styling: StyleSheet (React Native) + inline styles for web
- State: React hooks (useState, useEffect, useContext)
- Auth: Supabase Google OAuth 2.0
- Storage: AsyncStorage for session persistence
- PDF: html2pdf.js (web)
- Analytics: Mixpanel

### Supabase Rules
- Auth: autoRefreshToken: true, persistSession: true
- Storage: AsyncStorage
- ALWAYS call getValidSession() before any Supabase query
- NEVER query Supabase without a valid session guard
- Tables: invoices, clients, expenses, profiles, subscriptions
- All tables have RLS enabled with user_id policies

### Auth Rules
- Session helper: lib/supabase.ts → getValidSession()
- AuthContext: context/AuthContext.tsx
- ALWAYS use session.user.id for user_id in inserts
- clients table requires: name, user_id, freelancer_id (= user_id)
- On SIGNED_OUT redirect to /login
- Use .maybeSingle() NOT .single() to avoid 406 errors

### File Structure



### CarrotCash Design System
- Primary color: #ED13C4 (pink accent)
- Font: Clash Display (headings) + Bricolage Grotesque (body)
- Theme: Light with glassmorphism
- Cards: rgba(255,255,255,0.5) + backdrop-filter: blur(16px)
- Border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.6)

### Business Logic
- GST: 18% default (CGST + SGST or IGST by location)
- Multi-currency: INR ₹ and USD $
- Invoice format: INV-YYYYMM-XXX
- clients.freelancer_id = session.user.id always

### Code Style
- TypeScript strictly
- Functional components only
- Always handle loading + error states
- async/await only, no .then()
- Console.log with emoji prefixes:
  ✅ Success  ❌ Error  🔄 Loading  🔍 Debug

### What NOT To Do
- Never use .single() → use .maybeSingle()
- Never hardcode user IDs
- Never skip session guard before queries
- Never change RLS policies without asking
- Never touch DB schema without confirming
- Never use localStorage (not supported in Expo)
- Never install packages without npx expo install

