## SECTION 3: High-End UI/UX Design Constraints (Mandatory)
*(Apply when creating or updating any UI components)*

### Visual Language & Glassmorphism
- **Linear Gradient Cards:** MUST use `LinearGradient` from `expo-linear-gradient` for all card backgrounds
- **Defrost Components:** Implement `backdrop-filter: blur(16px) saturate(180%)` for premium depth
- **Tactile Edges:** Use 1px solid border with 10% white opacity (`rgba(255,255,255,0.1)`)

### Animation Engine (Reanimated + Gestures)
- **Smooth Entrance:** Every screen MUST have fade + slight scale up entrance animation
- **Interactive Gestures:** Use `react-native-gesture-handler` for modals and drag-to-dismiss
- **Layout Transitions:** Use Shared Element Transitions for screen navigation

### Bento Grid Layout Logic
- **Modular Design:** MUST use Bento Grid for dashboard features to ensure scannability
- **Visual Hierarchy:** Most important data (Total Revenue) gets largest box (2x2 or 3x2)
- **Compartmentalization:** Maintain strict visual boundaries between boxes

### Machine Experience (MX) UI
- **Activity Status:** Show "Machine Learning Prediction" or "Agent Activity" instead of loading spinners
- **Immediate Feedback:** Provide visual feedback (isAutoSet toggles) when agent modifies data

### Technical Requirements
- **Stack:** Expo SDK 55, Expo Router, NativeWind v5, Reanimated v3
- **Performance:** Use `FlatList` with optimized `renderItem` for financial lists
- **State:** Manage persistent UI states with React Context + AsyncStorage

